  "chapter": {
    "number": 58,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "True Fasts and Sabbaths"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Cry aloud, do not hold back!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Raise your voice like a ram’s horn.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Declare to My people their transgression",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to the house of Jacob their sins.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For day after day they seek Me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and delight to know My ways,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like a nation that does what is right",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and does not forsake the justice of their God.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "They ask Me for righteous judgments;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they delight in the nearness of God.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Why have we fasted,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and You have not seen?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Why have we humbled ourselves,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and You have not noticed?”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Behold, on the day of your fast, you do as you please,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and you oppress all your workers.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You fast with contention and strife",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to strike viciously with your fist.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You cannot fast as you do today",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and have your voice be heard on high.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is this the fast I have chosen:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a day for a man to deny himself,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to bow his head like a reed,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to spread out sackcloth and ashes?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Will you call this a fast",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a day acceptable to the LORD?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Isn’t this the fast that I have chosen:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to break the chains of wickedness,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to untie the cords of the yoke,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to set the oppressed free",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and tear off every yoke?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Isn’t it to share your bread with the hungry,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to bring the poor and homeless into your home,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to clothe the naked when you see him,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and not to turn away",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from your own flesh and blood?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then your light will break forth like the dawn,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your healing will come quickly.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Your righteousness will go before you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the glory of the LORD will be your rear guard.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then you will call, and the LORD will answer;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will cry out, and He will say, ‘Here I am.’",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "If you remove the yoke from your midst,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the pointing of the finger and malicious talk,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "and if you give yourself to the hungry",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and satisfy the afflicted soul,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "then your light will go forth in the darkness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and your night will be like noonday.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The LORD will always guide you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He will satisfy you in a sun-scorched land",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and strengthen your frame.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "You will be like a well-watered garden,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like a spring whose waters never fail.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your people will rebuild the ancient ruins;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you will restore the age-old foundations;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you will be called Repairer of the Breach,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Restorer of the Streets of Dwelling.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If you turn your foot from breaking the Sabbath,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from doing as you please on My holy day,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "if you call the Sabbath a delight,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the LORD’s holy day honorable,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "if you honor it by not going your own way",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or seeking your own pleasure or speaking idle words,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "then you will delight yourself in the LORD,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will make you ride on the heights of the land",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and feed you with the heritage of your father Jacob.”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "For the mouth of the LORD has spoken."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
